<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/1144438-meg-clayton"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1557339241i/1144438._UX100_CR0,0,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/1144438-meg-clayton">Meg Clayton</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Pretty much everything, Pamela -- thanks for asking. The events of the novel are drawn from their actual lives, based on a lot of research (detailed i<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Pretty much everything, Pamela -- thanks for asking. The events of the novel are drawn from their actual lives, based on a lot of research (detailed in the acknowledgments, but that is only the tip of the iceburg). So, for example, when Ernest uses the c-word ... I would not put that word in his mouth if I didn't have an account of him having said it.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
