<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/57803623-bull-durham"><img alt="" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_100x100-259587f1619f5253426a4fa6fb508831.png" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/57803623-bull-durham">Bull Durham</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">IMO somewhat like Blood Meridian - my favorite novel. Cormac did a lot of research and much in this extremely violent book is based on contemporary ac<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">IMO somewhat like Blood Meridian - my favorite novel. Cormac did a lot of research and much in this extremely violent book is based on contemporary accounts and actual people, places, things and happenings. And the dialog, of course, is invented, as is some (but not all) of the action.<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
